<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-07-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-07-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="455" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d455">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2489/66.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Squiers</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-07-22"><hi rend="italic">July 22,
                                1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Squiers reports that the minister for foreign affairs has
                            particularly requested him to ask the department for a categorical reply
                            to the proposal of Panama for the settlement of the <hi rend="italic">Columbia</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Buffalo</hi> cases, as Panama
                            desires to close the matter.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>